#8995 V850: Fix 26 SLEIGH bugs causing incorrect decompilation and disassembly
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Cross-referenced the V850E2M instruction manual and GCC's V850 backend
against Ghidra's SLEIGH implementation and fixed every semantic bug found.

Critical (wrong values computed):
 1. ST.W 23-bit: wrote halfword instead of word
 2. DIVHU: sign-extended unsigned operand via sext instead of zext
 3. DIVH (reg,reg): used unsigned sdiv on full 32-bit register instead of
    signed division on sign-extended lower halfword
 4. CVTF.DL: used int2float (int→float) instead of trunc (float→int),
    completely reversing the operation
 5. DIVQ/DIVQU reg2==reg3 overlap: quotient written after remainder, so
    quotient wins; manual says remainder must persist. Swapped write order
    to match DIV/DIVU and the architecture manual.

High (significantly degraded decompiler output):
 6. CMOV variants: multiply-by-boolean pattern unreadable; replaced with
    if/goto conditional
 7. MMIO not volatile: reads/writes to 0xFF400000-0xFFFFFFFF optimized away;
    added volatile range to pspec
 8. LDSR: dead-code eliminated with no side effect; added pcodeop
 9. either_or/either_or1 macros: multiply-by-boolean unreadable; replaced
    with if/goto
10. SATADD/SATSUB (all 7 forms): S and Z flags computed on pre-saturation
    result and opaque __saturate pcodeop hid saturation from decompiler;
    replaced with inline saturation logic with flags on saturated result

Medium (incorrect but less impactful):
11. BSH/BSW/HSW: zext of sub-register before shift lost upper bits
12. MULHI: operated on full 32-bit register instead of lower halfword
13. CAXI: unmasked write address and multiply-by-boolean pattern
14. DIVH (3-op): used unsigned sdiv instead of signed s/
15. DIV: result truncation via & mask instead of proper s/ and s%
16. DIVU: result truncation via & mask instead of proper / and %
17. DIVQ/DIVQU: same mask truncation issue as DIV/DIVU
18. Bit search (SCH0L/SCH0R/SCH1L/SCH1R): missing OV=0 and S=0 flag clears
19. set_CY_neg2 (SBF borrow flag): single comparison overflowed; replaced
    with two-step borrow check
20. FNMAF.S/FNMSF.S: used -1 f* for negation instead of f- unary negate

Low (cosmetic / minor):
21. TST1 bit,reg: display showed operands in wrong order vs manual
22. V850.cspec: 64-bit return join had r10/r11 swapped (piece1=r11,piece2=r10)
23-26. Float mnemonics: ABSF.D/NEGF.D/RECIPF.D/RSQRTF.D displayed wrong name

Reference: https://www.renesas.com/en/document/mah/v850e2m-users-manual-architecture
